        "title": "How to Become a Muslim",
        "body": "\n                    <h4>The Meaning of Accepting Islam</h4>\n                    <p>Becoming a Muslim means willingly submitting to Allah and acknowledging Muhammad (ﷺ) as His final messenger. The process is simple, beautiful, and does not require any specialized ceremony or priest.</p>\n                    \n                    <h4>The Step-by-Step Process</h4>\n                    <ol>\n                        <li><strong>Belief in the Heart:</strong> You must genuinely believe that there is only one God (Allah) worthy of worship and that Muhammad (ﷺ) is His final messenger.</li>\n                        <li><strong>Saying the Shahada:</strong> You must declare your faith verbally by reciting the Shahada. It is recommended, though not strictly required, to do this in front of witnesses (like your local Mosque Imam or Muslim friends).</li>\n                        <li><strong>Purification (Ghusl):</strong> After accepting Islam, it is a strongly recommended Sunnah to take a full-body ritual bath (Ghusl) to symbolize physical and spiritual purification.</li>\n                    </ol>\n\n                    <h4>Required Declarations (The Shahada)</h4>\n                    <p>To enter the fold of Islam, one recites the First Kalimah and the Second Kalimah.</p>\n                    \n                    <h5>First Kalimah (Tayyabah - Purity)</h5>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">لَا إِلٰهَ إِلَّا اللّٰهُ مُحَمَّدٌ رَسُولُ اللّٰهِ</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 La ilaha illallah, Muhammadur Rasulullah</div>\n                    <p>\"There is no deity but Allah, Muhammad is the Messenger of Allah.\"</p>\n\n                    <h5>Second Kalimah (Shahadah - Testimony)</h5>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">أَشْهَدُ أَنْ لَا إِلٰهَ إِلَّا اللّٰهُ وَحْدَهُ لَا شَرِيكَ لَهُ، وَأَشْهَدُ أَنَّ مُحَمَّدًا عَبْدُهُ وَرَسُولُهُ</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Ash-hadu an la ilaha illallahu wahdahu la sharika lahu, wa ash-hadu anna Muhammadan 'abduhu wa rasuluh</div>\n                    <p>\"I bear witness that there is no deity but Allah alone, without partner; and I bear witness that Muhammad is His servant and Messenger.\"</p>\n                ",
