        "body": "\n                    <h4>What is Sawm?</h4>\n                    <p>Fasting from dawn (Fajr) to sunset (Maghrib), abstaining from food, drink, smoking, and marital relations.</p>\n                    <h4>Niyyah (Intention)</h4>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">نَوَيْتُ أَنْ أَصُومَ غَدًا مِنْ شَهْرِ رَمَضَانَ الْمُبَارَكِ فَرْضًا لَكَ يَا اللَّهُ فَتَقَبَّلْ مِنِّي</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Nawaytu an asuma ghadan min shahri Ramadanal-mubaraki fardhan laka ya Allahu fataqabbal minni</div>\n                    <h4>Suhoor (Pre-Dawn Meal)</h4>\n                    <p>The Prophet ﷺ said: <em>\"Take suhoor, for indeed there is blessing in suhoor.\"</em> (Bukhari & Muslim)</p>\n                    <h4>Dua for Iftar</h4>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">اللَّهُمَّ لَكَ صُمْتُ وَعَلَى رِزْقِكَ أَفْطَرْتُ</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Allahumma laka sumtu wa 'ala rizqika aftartu</div>\n                    <p>\"O Allah, for You I have fasted and upon Your provision I have broken my fast.\"</p>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-arabic\">ذَهَبَ الظَّمَأُ وَابْتَلَّتِ الْعُرُوقُ وَثَبَتَ الْأَجْرُ إِنْ شَاءَ اللَّهُ</div>\n                    <div class=\"tutorial-pronunciation\">🔊 Dhahaba adh-dhama'u wabtallatil-'uruqu wa thabatal-ajru in sha Allah</div>\n                    <p>\"The thirst has gone, the veins are moistened, and the reward is assured, if Allah wills.\"</p>\n                    <h4>Who is Exempt?</h4>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>The sick or on medication</li>\n                        <li>Travelers</li>\n                        <li>Pregnant, breastfeeding, or menstruating women</li>\n                        <li>The elderly who cannot fast</li>\n                        <li>Children before puberty</li>\n                    </ul>\n                ",
